&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;**Please note that this vacancy is available to existing registered nurses only, if you are a student nurse, please contact the recruitment team on 0151 529 3030**&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse - Ward 25 (General Medicine)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent days and nights&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a current a Staff Nurse looking for a change?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to be part of a developing ward and work with a team that is dedicated to improving clinical outcomes for patients?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If yes, then Ward 25 is the place for you! Ward 25 is a Medical Ward within the Aintree site of Liverpool University Hospitals who are seeking enthusiastic and forward thinking Band 5 nurses to support us to develop and improve our service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer fixed term or permanent contracts, flexible working to support your work life balance and can include various shift patterns to suit your needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can work with you, providing support from our clinical educators and corporate teams which will develop your future career pathway. This could include you being supported with spoke hours into specific specialty which would interest you, i.e. tissue viability, clinical education.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to arrange an informal visit then we would be very happy to show you round and introduce you to our current team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Naomi Williams, Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;naomi.williams@liverpoolft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0151 529 8898&lt;/p&gt;
